## Project Summary

### Purpose

A launcher and orchestrator for pre-configured Claude Code agents. Each agent runs Claude Code CLI inside a Docker container with its own model, parameters, and system instructions, while sharing authentication, workspace, and custom slash commands. The user selects an agent from an interactive terminal menu and is dropped into a Claude Code session.

### Tech Stack

- **Python 3** — launcher script (`run.py`)
- **Docker + Docker Compose** — containerized Claude Code environments (Debian bookworm-slim base)
- **Claude Code CLI** — installed inside the container via `claude.ai/install.sh`
- **Python deps**: `pick` (interactive terminal picker), `python-dotenv` (`.conf` file parsing)

### Project Structure

```
run.py                  — entry point: agent picker → Docker launcher
Dockerfile              — builds Claude Code container image
docker-compose.yml      — service definition, volume mounts for state/auth/commands
agents/
  default.conf          — default env vars (Opus, max effort, thinking on)
  <name>.md             — agent system instructions (becomes CLAUDE.md in container)
  <name>.conf           — optional per-agent env var overrides
custom_commands/
  write-summary.md      — /write-summary slash command (project summary generator)
tips/                   — user-facing documentation files
TODO.txt                — feature backlog
```

### Architecture

`run.py` discovers agents by globbing `agents/*.md`, displays them via `pick`, loads the matching `.conf` (falling back to `default.conf`), syncs state to `~/.claude-agents/<name>/`, builds the Docker image, and execs `docker compose run`. The container mounts:

- `/ai_workspace` → `/workspace` (shared work directory)
- `~/.claude-agents/<name>/` → `/home/claude/.claude` (per-agent state)
- Shared `.claude.json` and `.credentials.json` (one-time OAuth, reused by all agents)
- `custom_commands/` → read-only slash commands
- `.claude_summary` → agent's `MEMORY.md` (shared project context across agents)

